DOROTHY F. BULKLEY v. WILLIAM G. ALBRECHT et al., SUPERVISORS OF ELECTIONS [No. 7,

October Term, 1936.]

Decided May 20th, 1936.

*698The cause was argued, as of the April Term, before Bond, C. J., Urner, Offutt, Parke, Sloan, Mitchell, Shehan, and Johnson, JJ.

Augustus C. Binswanger, with who was Enos S. Stockbridge on the brief, for the appellant. Herbert R. O’Conor, Attorney General,, and William L. Henderson and Charles T. LeVinness, 3rd, Assistant Attorney General, submitting on brief, for the appellees.

The opinion was delivered per Curiam.
